            // per-check context strings
            ["P7_KmsExplain"]    = ("KMS piracy operates in two forms: (1) LOCAL EMULATOR — a fake KMS server (KMSpico, vlmcsd) running on 127.x.x.x that tricks Windows locally; (2) CLOUD SERVICE — a third-party internet KMS host (e.g. km8.msguides.com) that anyone can configure Windows to use. Microsoft does NOT provide public KMS servers — any internet-facing KMS host is an unauthorized activation service.",
